Marriage Customs in Tibet
    - Monogamy
    - Polygyny
    - Polyandry
    - Polyandrygyny
        - Only common with aristocrats
Economic customs dictated the type of marriage most suitable to a given family
Weddings in Tibet
    - Marriage was not a religious rite, it was a social rite
    - Not a sacrament and lamas didn't play a large role in ceremonies
    - Usually arranged by parents of the bride and groom
    - Eloping not forbidden
    - Concerns about incest and social status
Masculinity and Gender
    - Public displays of affection between men
    - Tibet is a 'homosocial' society
    - Monks will send love letters to other monks; breakups can also occur (boyfriends)
